oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Federal Chemical Company
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of a building on the grounds of the Federal Chemical Company in Mount Pleasant. A group of unidentified people can be seen standing next to the building on right. Federal Chemical Company was one of the many fertilizer plants operating in Mount Pleasant during the phosphate boom of the 1920s-1960s.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Fertilizer industry; Smokestacks; People
